result.execSummary:
All charges against Rudy Alvarez Gaona in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Rudy Alvarez Gaona is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defense motions to exclude lab testing results at trial. Motion GRANTED.  State motions for dismissal. Court ordered case DISMISSED without prejudice. Jury Trial set for 10/10/2022 is vacated.
Received and filed:  Original Transcript of Proceedings commencing 6/23/2022  (10 pages) and Certification of Filing Transcript.

Court schedules Final Pretrial Conference and Jury Trial dates and sets the following deadlines:  09/26/2022 for filing of Jury Instructions, Motions in Limine, Witness lists and Change of Plea forms and 09/26/2022 for State to provide crime lab reports. 
Matter adjourned to Br. 9.  Final pre-trial scheduled for October 6, 2022 at 02:00 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Case is adjourned to Branch 17.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 4.  Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.
